      public ArrayList<String> generateStringSingleValueList(int lengthOfDataSet, boolean printTheDataSet, boolean printTheDataSetInArrayFormat, boolean printWithQuotes)
      This function returns an list of random strings
      Parameters:
      lengthOfDataSet - It should be an integer value that determines the number of random strings you want to generate.
      printTheDataSet - It should be a boolean value that determines whether you want print the list.
      printTheDataSetInArrayFormat - It should be a boolean value that determines whether you want print the list in an array format like [a,assa,aaas,...] or ["a","assa","aaas",...].
      printWithQuotes - It should be a boolean value that determines whether you want print the list with or without quotes, true for with quotes([aa,aaa,...]) and false for without quotes(["aa","aaa",...])
      Returns:
      This returns an list of random strings.
